    // Update condition
    while (!correct || attempts &lt;= 3) {
    
        // Update variable at the end of the loop
        attempts++;
    }

A do-while loop is best suited for this. 
It is guaranteed to execute at least once, validate the loop condition at the end of the loop instead of the beginning, and it&#39;s easy to break out of any loop when you have breaking condition like this.

    int guesses = 0;
    final maxGuesses = 3;
